name: Celeste
desc: Madelines journey to the summit of Celeste Mountain.

chapters.name: Prologue
chapters.desc: Madeline arrives at the foot of the mountain. A lone cabin stands at the top of a broken driveway, housing an unlikely resident. And so she begins... a long, long upward climb.

chapters.name: Forsaken City
chapters.desc: A deserted city stands in Madeline's path. The deep pits and crumbling wreckage give her pause, but she finds comfort in the companionship of a fellow traveler.

chapters.name: Old Site
chapters.desc: Madeline awakens to find the mountain betraying its disturbing nature. She unearths a mysterious chamber where a familar presence is fettered.

chapters.name: Celestial Resort
chapters.desc: Seeking passage through an abandoned estate, Madeline takes an unwise detour and encounters more than dust and echos.

chapters.name: Golden Ridge
chapters.desc: Madeline scales the sheer cliffs of the ridge; through a tempest that pushes back her every step. A single slip and she will be lost like a feather in the wind.

chapters.name: Mirror Temple
chapters.desc: An ancient temple in the side of the mountain houses a terrible power. Madeline ventures in to find her friend and learns what lies inside her heart.

chapters.name: Reflection
chapters.desc: Madeline opens up to Theo under the stars and discovers that discarding your problems isn't easy. You can't climb out of a hole you dug yourself without facing your own reflection.

chapters.name: The Summit
chapters.desc: Whole again with renewed determination, Madeline begins her final ascent to the summit of the mountain.

chapters.name: Epilogue
chapters.desc: Back in the Old Woman's home at the end of her journey, Madeline enjoys the warmth of good company.

chapters.name: Core
chapters.desc: One year later, Madeline returns to discover the mountain's final secret; that which lies at the heart of everything.

chapters.name: Farewell
chapters.desc: Denial. Anger. Depression. Bargaining. Acceptance. Sometimes, one of the hardest things in life is saying farewell.
